BEIJING, Dec. 15 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Vladimir Putin said Wednesday that Russia-China relations are a paradigm of international relations in the 21st century. At a virtual meeting with Chinese President Xi Jinping, Putin said Russia-China relations are now at their best in history. Their relations embody a high degree of strategic mutual trust and have set an example of mutual benefit based on non-interference in each other's internal affairs and mutual respect for each other's interests, Putin noted. Enditem